A 17-year-old girl has been ambushed and gang-raped by three armed boys,suspected to be street urchins, in Ado-Ekiti, the Ekiti State capital. The Nation learnt that the teenager was hawking sachet waters and soft drinks around 7pm on Monday when she was attacked at the popular Ojaâ€™ba market in Ado-Ekiti metropolis. It was gathered that the victim, who was with the three boys who were armed with broken bottles for about 45 minutes, was raped under compulsion. She was later taken to an undisclosed to the hospital for medical treatment after which the incident was reported to the Ekiti Police Command and Office of the Wife of Ekiti State Governor, Mrs Erelu Fayemi. Our correspondent gathered from a credible source that the medical bill of the victim was offset by Mrs Fayemi. When contacted, the Ekiti State Police Public Relations Officer, Sunday Abutu confirmed the incident, saying two suspects have been arrested in connection with the gang-rape. Abutu noted that the Command has commenced investigation into the matter, assuring that the case would be thoroughly prosecuted and ensure justice prevail. He,lamented the increasing incidences of sexual against women, adding that the Command was ready to go against all odds to prevent the state from being tagged a thriving land for violence against girl-child.